{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"dozy-groggy-tilefish","description":"## Why\nautodeploy v1 signals AUTODEPLOY_ERROR reason=config_manual once for a DEPLOYED..TARGET range, then deployed-sha advances and the signal never repeats — there is no pending-work ledger. The manual apply for d1e4cd5c (replication/g2p/refs-meta config) was signalled during incident 2731's recovery and has NOT been performed.\n## What\n- Perform (or explicitly rule out) the d1e4cd5c manual operator apply on the box.\n- Add a durable pending-manual-apply marker (state file + repeated signal or alarm) so unactioned config_manual work cannot be silently swallowed.\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] d1e4cd5c manual apply performed or documented as not required.\n- [ ] config_manual signals persist (re-emitted or alarmed) until acknowledged.\n- [ ] File paths: infra/scripts/autodeploy.sh.","id":"e983-4df0-0d53-4811","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"autodeploy config_manual signal is fire-and-forget: d1e4cd5c's replication/g2p/refs-meta manual apply is pending and untracked"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783659018686288001,"uuid":"6ee3d814-25fa-4466-ac5b-6e454f581448"}